HEADWORD: Midheaven
<hw>Mid"heav`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
midst or middle of heaven or the sky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The meridian, or middle line of
the heavens; the point of the ecliptic on the meridian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>midiron</ent>⟦br⟧
